	</div><div class="blogs_entrybody" style="clear:both">
		I've had some interesting e-mail responses on this case, and I was surprised that none of the linux wonks that read my blog figured out how Kiltlifter's workstation was incorrectly mounting volumes on the workstation.<br/><br/>I peppered the case file entries with clues.  I'll throw a few specifics out, and let you guys discuss them.  Perhaps I should have gone into more detail in the case file entries, but part of my goal in writing these is to make everyone think very hard and apply your unique experiences.<br/><br/>1) The workstations were running Gentoo Linux.  How is Gentoo different than other Linux distributions? (Think of how Gentoo is initially installed and configured.)<br/><br/>2) The vendor installed the SAN and literally 'left'.  There was no IT support.  Kiltlifter and Dunnit had basic linux administration knowledge.<br/><br/>3) The Linux kernel (and modules) have a tendency to assign device IDs "as they are found".  Depending on how the hardware responds to certain requests, identification can vary.  How could this have played a part?<br/><br/>4) This was (relatively speaking) a small research lab (high security area) with few researchers, few workstations, and few clues.  Could this have played a part in how the network and SAN were installed and integrated?<br/><br/>A few of you have made some good points which got me thinking that this case requires a little more frosting on the cupcake.  I certainly don't want to leave anyone confused.<br/><br/>Discuss!<br/><br/>Chief<br/><hr><br/><p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710090931/http://www.numly.com/numly/verify.asp?id=80153-061207-718666-50"><img alt="numly esn" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710090931im_/http://numly.com/numly/icon.asp?id=8015306120771866650" border="0"> 80153-061207-718666-50<br><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710090931im_/http://numly.com/numly/barcode.asp?code=8015306120771866650&amp;height=20&amp;width=1&amp;mode=code39"></a><br><br>Â© 2006 All Rights Reserved.</p><p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
